- What's the matter with you?

149
00:14:21,480 --> 00:14:24,563
Have some respect for him,
for his family.

150
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:29,449
You got hurt, but you're here.
You're alive.

151
00:14:33,840 --> 00:14:35,569
Listen to me,

152
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:38,044
we move on.

153
00:14:38,560 --> 00:14:41,689
What's here and now,
that's all that matters, all right?

154
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:45,129
Go back to your wife.

155
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:51,850
If you need help,

156
00:14:52,320 --> 00:14:53,765
you can always find me.

157
00:14:54,520 --> 00:14:57,251
We stick together, all of us.

158
00:14:57,320 --> 00:15:00,529
Have you moved on, sir?
From what happened?

159
00:15:23,760 --> 00:15:24,966
Hello?

160
00:15:25,040 --> 00:15:27,281
A car will be downstairs
in 15 minutes.

161
00:15:35,920 --> 00:15:37,001
I'm Mark.

162
00:15:52,560 --> 00:15:54,050
Baby daughter.

163
00:16:25,680 --> 00:16:29,048
Take the path through the wood.
You'll find her at the other end.

164
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:32,526
Bit of a walk.

165
00:16:34,320 --> 00:16:37,085
You've seen the news.
20 dead, scores injured.

166
00:16:37,960 --> 00:16:40,691
Semtex was used. You understand?

167
00:16:44,640 --> 00:16:46,483
Perpetrator?

168
00:16:46,560 --> 00:16:48,847
It was strapped to his jacket,
self-detonated.

169
00:16:48,920 --> 00:16:53,721
No details on who he was.
CCTV have no clear images.

170
00:16:54,320 --> 00:16:55,731
There's nothing left of him.

171
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:57,564
We're bound by procedure.

172
00:16:57,880 --> 00:17:00,360
In this situation,
we cannot afford those constraints.

173
00:17:00,440 --> 00:17:03,683
This is off-reservation.
It's why you're at my home.

174
00:17:03,800 --> 00:17:06,007
I want you to find who's responsible

175
00:17:06,080 --> 00:17:08,890
and stop him
in whatever way you feel fit.

176
00:17:08,960 --> 00:17:10,644
Let it be done quickly.

177
00:17:11,920 --> 00:17:14,605
It'll be you and Mark.
He's young but capable.

178
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:16,284
Very good with a gun, I hear.

179
00:17:16,360 --> 00:17:19,170
I want it low-tech, old trade craft.

180
00:17:20,040 --> 00:17:22,122
If you get caught,
I don't want evidence.

181
00:17:22,320 --> 00:17:25,130
I'll supply technical backup
and the sweep and clean.

182
00:17:25,360 --> 00:17:29,251
No luck yet with the tracer
you planted in the Semtex

183
00:17:29,320 --> 00:17:32,210
but we did find something curious
of your man Harry.

184
00:17:33,160 --> 00:17:36,130
No bullets in his automatic.
Any thoughts?

185
00:17:37,960 --> 00:17:39,371
Maybe.

186
00:17:40,560 --> 00:17:43,882
You're my hands on this, Ewan,
my conscience.

187
00:17:45,640 --> 00:17:46,721
Wipe it clean.

188
00:17:48,280 --> 00:17:49,725
No loose ends.

189
00:18:21,840 --> 00:18:23,410
Where's Harry?

190
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:26,207
Fat cheapskate owes me money.

191
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:30,211
Harry's dead.

192
00:18:32,840 --> 00:18:36,208
I want you to think carefully,
more carefully than you've ever thought.

193
00:18:36,280 --> 00:18:37,645
Was there anything...

194
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:41,321
Anything unusual happened
in the last few days?

195
00:18:41,760 --> 00:18:45,481
Anything you know
but you're not telling me?

196
00:18:45,920 --> 00:18:47,922
Dead? What are you talking about?

197
00:18:55,840 --> 00:18:56,966
I'm leaving.

198
00:18:59,480 --> 00:19:01,687
