Why?

199
00:19:01,840 --> 00:19:03,763
I don't know what you're talking about.

200
00:19:09,760 --> 00:19:12,604
I don't have time to waste.

201
00:19:12,680 --> 00:19:15,251
I know you know something
and I'm not leaving until you talk,

202
00:19:15,320 --> 00:19:18,005
- one way or another.

203
00:19:25,600 --> 00:19:26,726
Talk.

204
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:29,041
I don't know anything. Please.

205
00:19:31,440 --> 00:19:33,761
By the time I'm through with your face,

206
00:19:33,840 --> 00:19:36,923
nobody's going to wanna look at you,
let alone pay to fuck you.

207
00:19:37,880 --> 00:19:39,769
He said nothing would happen.

208
00:19:40,840 --> 00:19:41,966
What?

209
00:19:42,040 --> 00:19:44,168
- He told me it was just business.
- Who did?

210
00:19:44,240 --> 00:19:47,050
- A client.
- Which client? Tell me about him.

211
00:19:47,120 --> 00:19:49,327
- Young guy, said his name was Paul.
- Paul?

212
00:19:49,400 --> 00:19:52,768
I saw him regular for two months.
He wanted to know stuff about Harry.

213
00:19:52,840 --> 00:19:55,127
- What stuff?
- What he was up to, his routine,

214
00:19:55,280 --> 00:19:56,930
he paid me extra.

215
00:19:57,000 --> 00:20:01,005
I told him useless stuff-
who he met, what time, his routine,

216
00:20:01,080 --> 00:20:03,401
- just useless stuff.
- What about the bullets?

217
00:20:03,480 --> 00:20:05,164
Said it was a joke to take them out.

218
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:07,527
Said Harry showed up with a gun.
He wanted to teach him a lesson.

219
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:09,364
Where did you meet him?
What did he look like?

220
00:20:09,440 --> 00:20:11,408
At his house. Expensive place.

221
00:20:11,480 --> 00:20:14,802
Short hair, brown, slim,
could pass for Greek or Italian

222
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:15,847
but he was an Arab.

223
00:20:15,920 --> 00:20:17,570
- How do you know?
- I have Arab friends.

224
00:20:17,640 --> 00:20:20,564
I know what the language sounds like.
Heard him speaking it on the phone.

225
00:20:20,640 --> 00:20:22,449
You know his address?

226
00:20:31,840 --> 00:20:35,162
When the bomb went off,
there was a flash,

227
00:20:35,240 --> 00:20:37,049
and then there was lots of smoke.

228
00:20:37,120 --> 00:20:40,567
A lot of glass flying. There was
a lot of people on the ground.

229
00:20:40,640 --> 00:20:43,007
Horrendous, huge explosion...

230
00:20:43,840 --> 00:20:46,207
I don't know.
I just felt it more than anything else.

231
00:20:52,320 --> 00:20:53,731
Ash.

232
00:20:57,080 --> 00:20:58,605
Jesus.

233
00:20:59,080 --> 00:21:00,491
How have you been?

234
00:21:00,560 --> 00:21:03,211
Good, yeah. You?

235
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:05,370
Yeah, I'm good.

236
00:21:05,720 --> 00:21:07,643
Do you, uh, live around here?

237
00:21:07,720 --> 00:21:10,041
No, I'm just... Coffee.

238
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:12,604
It's good to see you.

239
00:21:13,040 --> 00:21:14,530
Yeah, you too.

240
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:19,487
I have to go. I'm late for something.

241
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:22,571
Listen, um...
Do you have a number?

242
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:26,680
If you...
If you give me yours, I can...

243
00:21:27,560 --> 00:21:30,006
- If I can get this thing to work.
- It's all right, give me yours.

244
00:21:30,080 --> 00:21:31,366
I'll tap into this.

245
00:21:31,440 --> 00:21:34,364
Um... OK.

246
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:36,602
07950...

247
00:21:38,880 --> 00:21:40,723
956958.

248
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:44,408
- Got it.

249
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:49,325
Look, I have to go.
I'm really late for something, but...

250
00:21:50,120 --> 00:21:51,406
Really nice to see you again.

251
00:21:54,240 --> 00:21:56,846
Horrific.
What we saw was devastation.

252
00:21:56,920 --> 00:21:59,400
It was just horrific, really.
It was like being in a war zone.

253
00:21:59,480 --> 00:22:01,130
It was crazy and I heard screams.

254
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:04,124
People like, kind of injured,
and their clothes were all, like...

255
00:22:04,200 --> 00:22:05,531
Everyone was just covered in dust.

256
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:08,046
We have with us
today Crispin Jones,

257
00:22:08,120 --> 00:22:09,610
who is an intelligence expert.

